fulltitle: Rare George Shearing Radio Interview from 1972
description: George left us in 2011 at the age of 91.  He was an awesome jazz piano player who had the most popular quintet in the country in the 50s and 60s.  He had a unique method of playing chords in sync with a vibraphone that gave him the "Shearing Sound".  But, he could also play classical, popular, even some roaring honky tonk piano.  I was a Denver radio DJ ("Don Mueller") in 1972, and had a chance to interview George.  He was blind, but could hit notes perfectly, better than anybody I know!   So, since I save tapes, I decided to share this with you!
